title: Bangladesh success story for emergency vaccination campaigns in Cox’s Bazar
description: Rapid and massive vaccination campaigns in Cox’s Bazar have helped prevent outbreaks of deadly diseases such as cholera, and rapidly curtail diphtheria and measles in the Rohingya camps and adjoining areas. WHO is working with the Ministry of Health Bangladesh and partners to roll out successful vaccination campaigns to save lives.
channelTitle: World Health Organization South-East Asia Region - WHO SEARO
